ColumnDefinitions.Name: Time1
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Time in ms (0 = the start of the animation) when the Alpha will be the Desired Alpha value. Note that it will slowly transition to that value, so if you want the transition to be quicker, add a new ALPHA metadata tag, make it apply just before this one, and give it a "1" desired value.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Unknown Field
ColumnDefinitions.Description: 0, 1, or 83 so far. It's apparently not VFX Filter ID.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Desired Alpha
ColumnDefinitions.Description: This might be a %, 0 = invisible and 1 = visible.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Start Time
ColumnDefinitions.Description: The starting time for when the prop is visible, in miliseconds. 0 = the beginning of the animation

ColumnDefinitions.Name: End Time
ColumnDefinitions.Description: The ending time for when the prop is visibile, in miliseconds. 0 = the beginning of the animation

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Bombardment Order
ColumnDefinitions.Description: This is related to bombardment abilities, allowing props to be toggled off after using a unit's ability. The number here is the order in which the prop is toggled off. Look at the gyrobomber's stuff to see this in action.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Prop Model
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Path to the prop's model. Probably has to be of the "rigid" vertex type, so no rigged models.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Bone ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: This is the ID of the bone to which the prop is attached. The bone is also the origin for positioning/rotating the prop.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Animation Speed Scale
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Likely speeds up/slows down rider animations. I wonder if this can be used to correct that cavalry scaling bug...

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Start Time
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Removes animation frames before this time, in milliseconds.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: End Time
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Removes animation frames after this time, in milliseconds.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Scale
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Unit will go to this scale between start and end time? Haven't test it yet, sounds funny though.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: ID of the entry, normally left as 0

ColumnDefinitions.Name: BoneID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: ID of the bone to which the prop is attached. The prop is the origin for positioning and rotation. Can be -1

ColumnDefinitions.Name: ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: ID of the entry, normally left as 0

ColumnDefinitions.Name: BoneID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: ID of the bone to which the prop is attached. The prop is the origin for positioning and rotation. Can be -1

ColumnDefinitions.Name: StartTime
ColumnDefinitions.Description: When the projectile will fire, time in miliseconds. 0 = start of the animation.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Position
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Measured from the unit's animroot bone, in meters.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Time1
ColumnDefinitions.Description: When the face pose will be applied, in miliseconds. 0 = beginning of animation.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Face Pose ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: This should probably be an enum. (these are animation slots available in .frg, and in the order they appear there) 0=FACE_POSE_RELAX,1=FACE_POSE_RELAX_BLINK,2=FACE_POSE_ANGRY,3=FACE_POSE_ANGRY_BLINK,4=FACE_POSE_ANGRY_SCREAM,5=FACE_POSE_DEAD,6=FACE_POSE_DEAD2,7=FACE_POSE_DEATH_SCREAM,8=FACE_POSE_WORRIED,9=FACE_POSE_WORRIED_BLINK

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Unknown Field
ColumnDefinitions.Description: It's mostly 1's but some 0.6 to 0.8, so it could be some "intensity" thing, no idea though.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: StartTime
ColumnDefinitions.Description: When the VFX will appear, in milliseconds. 0 = beginning of animation.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Filter
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Unsure what this is, always empty

ColumnDefinitions.Name: VFX Filter ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: This is related to that one column in the "battle entities tables". If this is 0, then the VFX will always show, but if it's anything else, then the battle entity of the unit needs to match this ID for the VFX to show up for that unit.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: VFX Name
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Name of the VFX's .xml file in the vfx folder. Leave off the file extension. Note that for this you don't need to add custom vfx to the particles db table and they still require a "movie"-type .pack for them to be loaded.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: NodeIndex
ColumnDefinitions.Description: ID of the bone to which the VFX is attached.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: VFX Scale
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Scale of the VFX. 1 = normal, 0.5 = half, etc.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Position
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Measured from the unit's animroot bone. In meters.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Time1
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Time when hand is posed. 0 = start of animation.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Left Hand Pose ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: This should be an enum. (these are animation slots in .frg) 0=HAND_POSE_RELAX,1=HAND_POSE_FLAT,2=HAND_POSE_CLENCH,3=HAND_POSE_GRIP,4=HAND_POSE_HALF_OPEN,5=HAND_POSE_THUMB_GRIP,6=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_1,7=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_2,8=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_3,9=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_4,10=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_5,11=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_6,12=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_7,13=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_8,14=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_9,15=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_10,

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Time1
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Time when hand is posed. 0 = start of animation.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Right Hand Pose ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: This should be an enum. (these are animation slots in .frg) 0=HAND_POSE_RELAX,1=HAND_POSE_FLAT,2=HAND_POSE_CLENCH,3=HAND_POSE_GRIP,4=HAND_POSE_HALF_OPEN,5=HAND_POSE_THUMB_GRIP,6=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_1,7=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_2,8=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_3,9=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_4,10=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_5,11=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_6,12=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_7,13=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_8,14=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_9,15=HAND_POSE_CUSTOM_10,

ColumnDefinitions.Name: StartTime
ColumnDefinitions.Description: When the bone goes to that transformed state.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: EndTime
ColumnDefinitions.Description: When the bone returns to it's original state? Not sure about that, but ff start and end times are the same, it'll stay transformed until the end of the animation.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: TargetNode
ColumnDefinitions.Description: ID of the bone which you are moving or rotating.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Position
ColumnDefinitions.Description: In meters. Local to the bone's orientation.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: EndTime
ColumnDefinitions.Description: If start = end time, will go until the end of the animation.

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Max Target Size
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Likely an enum related to unit size. Maybe 0=large, 1=medium, 2=small, 3=very_large, 4=very_small

ColumnDefinitions.Name: Min Target Size
ColumnDefinitions.Description: Likely an enum related to unit size. Maybe 0=large, 1=medium, 2=small, 3=very_large, 4=very_small

ColumnDefinitions.Name: ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: 0 or 1, probably linked to something in DB

ColumnDefinitions.Name: ID
ColumnDefinitions.Description: 0 or 1, probably linked to something in DB

ColumnDefinitions.Name: GenericBoneIndex
ColumnDefinitions.Description: -1 applies the whole animation? | The spliced animation applies to this bone and all of it's children. -1 seems to be the same as 0, ie. animroot, but there's probably something with the pose-type .anim files that makes it distinct.

ColumnDefinitions.Description: 0="Weapon Bone 1" in .frg but "be_prop_0" in a typical VMD. 1="Weapon Bone 2" in .frg but "be_prop_1" in VMD. etc.
